  "text": "To analyze the percentage of MSC that were at different stages of cell cycle a DNA analysis was performed. MSC from cases 8, 9, 10, 13 and 14 were harvested at 3rd passage, and the pellet was washed with PBS. Cells were incubated at room temperature with ribonuclease (40 U/ml) (Sigma Diagnostics Inc.) for 10 min, and later with 1 mg/ml propidium iodide (Sigma Diagnostics) for 15 min also at room temperature. The PI fluorescence was measured using the FACSCalibur flow cytometer, and the analysis was performed with the Paint-A-Gate software. [CITATION_1] ",
